This file describes changes to FeedbackHelper since the initial release.

5.3 (2025-12-18)
  - Allow reordering of custom phrases.
  - When overwriting files during export, attempt to move old files to trash.
  - Change package names to match Java conventions (internal).

5.2 (2025-12-15)
  - New grade visualisation system using JFreeChart instead of Tablesaw.
  - Feedback boxes are no longer modified when alt-tabbing to other apps.
  - Searching for submissions in directory is more permissive.
  - Bug fix: grade chooser no longer updates wrong student.

5.1 (2025-12-05)
  - Change zoom level input method to a dialog box.
  - Exported feedback documents now have fewer blank lines.

5.0 (2025-12-01)
  - Major reworking of internals, conforming more cleanly to MVC pattern and modern Java standards.
  - Target Java version changed to 17.
  - New software deployment system using jDeploy, simplifying installation and allowing auto-updates.
  - Removed dependencies:
    - nitrite database
    - json-simple
    - slf4j
  - Functionality improvements:
    - Custom phrases are now per-section.
    - Custom phrases can now be deleted.
    - Assignments can be created with no students.
    - Student IDs other than 9-digit numerics can be used.
    - Student list files are less strict, and compatible with MMS templates.
    - Saving is done to a single ".fht" file instead of 3 database files.
    - Backups are created every 15 minutes.
    - Exported grades are sorted by ID (Yichen).
  - Wide range of UI improvements:
    - Resizing behaviour and use of space improved across the UI.
    - UI scaling added (requires restart).
    - Preview panel replaced with concise list of students showing grade and feedback length.
    - Phrases are not truncated in phrase panel.
    - New "FH" logo icon added instead of default Java logo.
    - Status bar added to bottom of feedback screen.
    - Redesigned "Create Assignment" screen with more intuitive workflow.
    - FlatLaf Light theme set as default.
    - Errors are shown more consistently via popups.
    - Exporting automatically opens the file location in the desktop file manager.
    - Bullet points are added and removed more intelligently.
    - Unicode bullet symbol now allowed for line marker.
    - Grades are entered with a spinner control.
    - Removal of some redundant "confirm" or "save" buttons (Yichen).
    - Redundant "Insights" tab removed.
  - Other usability improvements:
    - FHT files can be opened directly in the desktop using file associations.
    - Last opened assignment is shown automatically on choosing Load Assignment.
    - Autosave is more frequent and no longer blocks UI actions.
    - New windows are centered properly on creation.
    - Mac copy-paste using Cmd+XCV added.
  - Bug fixes:
    - Leading 0 is not trimmed from student IDs (Yichen).
    - Asterisk line marker no longer prevents phrase recognition.
    - Many others.

4.0 (2024-02-22)
  - New option to add students to an assignment after starting (Femi).
  - Assignment files are now portable (can be loaded after being moved on disk) (Femi).
  - Sections can now be renamed (Femi).
  - Export of grades and feedback unified into one button (Femi).
  - About window added (Femi).
  - Hyphens are no longer removed from reusable comments (Femi).
  - Breaking: assignments created with FeedbackHelper 3.x cannot be loaded.

3.1 (2022-12-13)
  - Sentiment analysis removed, for performance.
  - Choice of colour themes, including FlatLaf and any built-in themes.
  - Storage of user preferences (currently only used for themes).
  - Images pre-loaded to cut UI lag when switching between sections.
  - Splash screens removed.
  - Bug fix: new windows can no longer be created with title bar off-screen.

3.0 (2022-11-21)
  - Almost identical to 3.0-rc.2, which seems to be stable.
  - Tweaked stdout messages.

3.0-rc.2 (2022-11-15)
  - Bug fix: phrase database path is now formed correctly.
  - Phrase database file is now closed properly after reading.
  - More verbose terminal output.
  - Adjust colours slightly.

3.0-rc.1 (2022-11-14)
  - Phrases database is now a simple json file, <assignment>-phrases.json
  - Removed dependency on neo4j.
  - Reintroduces support for older Java versions (anything 8+ should work).
  - Document database filename is now <assignment>-documents.no2 (more descriptive than .db).
  - Insights such as "These phrases are often used together" will no longer appear.

2.0 (2022-11-07)
  - Targets Java 17 instead of Java 11.
  - neo4j dependency updated from 3.5.1 to 5.1.0 to allow Java >11.
  - Java versions below 17 are no longer supported.
  - Breaking: assignments created with FeedbackHelper 1.x will not work.
  - Generated JAR files now have a more concise filename.

1.2 (2022-05-12)
  - Maven execution option "mvn exec:java" added (Michael).
  - Performance improvement for adding feedback to big projects (Michael).

1.1 (2021-12-22)
  - Tool will now guess student IDs based on directory structure, if manifest file not specified (Johannes).
  - A search box is now available to allow the user to filter used phrases (Michael).
  - Settings can now be edited in the manual screen after loading from a config file (Johannes).
  - Improved scrolling (Johannes).
  - Sentiments are now cached to improve performance (Johannes).
  - Loading screens now display more reliably across platforms (Michael).
  - Grades output file extension is now csv instead of txt (Michael).

1.0 (2021-10-06)
  - Initial release with source code as submitted by Bhuvan for CS5099 project.
